Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pour the boiled water into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @egg noodle nest{2} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

While the noodles cook, heat the @sesame oil{20%ml} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion, pepper and @sliced mushrooms{120%g}. Stir-fry until just soft, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Whilst the veg cooks, trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Once the veg has softened, add the garlic, @ginger puree{15%g} and @curry powder mix{2%tsp}. Cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @teriyaki sauce{150%ml}, cooked noodles and carrot ribbons into the cooked veg. Toss until coated and piping hot.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the hakka inspired noodles between your #bowls{}.

Finish with a scattering of @cashew nuts{25%g} over the top. Enjoy!